nd features real events and historical figures from that period, including feudal lord Oda Nobunaga. It will be <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/assassins-creed-shadows-brings-stealthy-mayhem-to-feudal-japan-on-november-15-180139119.html">available worldwide</a> on November 15.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> While Guillemot didn&#39;t say which titles Ubisoft is remaking, <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://kotaku.com/assassin-s-creed-4-black-flag-remake-skull-bones-1850596271"><em>Kotaku</em></a> previously reported that it&#39;s working on a new version of <em>Black Flag</em> .这款动作冒险游戏于 2013 年发布，以 18 世纪的海盗为主题，是该系列中最受欢迎的游戏之一。 Ubisoft is also expected to launch a new platform called &quot;Animus hub&quot; that players can use to launch and play games from the franchise on the same day <em>Shadows</em> drops. Animus hub, formerly known as <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/assassins-creed-infinity-live-online-game-service-135340262.html">Infinity</a> , could be potentially be a store, as well, and if that&#39;s true, then it makes sense for Ubisoft to work on more AC releases that it can sell through the hub.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/ubisoft-ceo-says-assassins-creed-remakes-are-in-the-works-035852195.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/ubisoft-ceo-says-assassins-creed-remakes-are-in-the-works-035852195.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e0de7c21-1d33-4d25-9383-d9c044958005</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mariella Moon]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jun 2024 03:58:52 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1719547069</ingested><modified> 2024-06-28T03:58:12+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="875" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-06%2Fabdf79c0-34fb-11ef-bebe-88fb6443a06c&amp;resize=1400%2C875&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=ec7e007e5ecfcf997f95463f7c9f8f1a5aa8c6d1" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="875" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-06%2Fabdf79c0-34fb-11ef-bebe-88fb6443a06c&amp;resize=1400%2C875&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=7dfbcd81fe6a051f8dfc304fd2b92ee4ea1558fa" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Ubisoft]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A computer graphic image of a man wearing a hood, holding two swords in knee-deep waters with a ship in the background.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Assassin's Creed]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Please don’t get your news from AI chatbots]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>这是对你的定期提醒，人工智能驱动的聊天机器人仍然会编造一些东西，并充满信心地撒谎，就像 GPS 系统告诉你回家的最近路是开车穿过湖一样。</p><p> My reminder comes courtesy of <em>Nieman Lab</em> , which <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.niemanlab.org/2024/06/chatgpt-is-hallucinating-fake-links-to-its-news-partners-biggest-investigations/"><ins>ran an experiment</ins></a> to see if ChatGPT would provide correct links to articles from news publications it pays millions of dollars to.事实证明 ChatGPT 没有。相反，它自信地组成了整个 URL，这种现象被人工智能行业称为“幻觉”，这个术语似乎更适合那些沉迷于自己的废话的真实的人。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> <em>Nieman Lab</em> ’s Andrew Deck asked the service to provide links to high-profile, exclusive stories published by 10 publishers that OpenAI has struck deals worth millions of dollars with. These included the <em>Associated Press</em> , <em>The Wall Street Journal</em> , the <em>Financial Times</em> , <em>The Times</em> (UK), <em>Le Monde</em> , <em>El País</em> , <em>The Atlantic</em> , <em>The Verge</em> , <em>Vox</em> , and <em>Politico</em> .作为回应，ChatGPT 回吐了导致 404 错误页面的虚构 URL，因为它们根本不存在。换句话说，系统完全按照设计运行：预测故事 URL 最有可能的版本，而不是实际引用正确的版本。 <em>Nieman Lab</em> did a similar experiment with a single publication — <em>Business Insider</em> — earlier this month and <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.niemanlab.org/2024/06/insider-union-chatgpt-hallucinating-links-business-insider-articles-openai-deal/"><ins>got the same result</ins></a> .</p><p> OpenAI 发言人告诉<em>Nieman Lab</em> ，该公司仍在构建“一种将对话功能与最新新闻内容相结合的体验，确保正确的归属和源材料的链接——这种增强的体验仍在开发中，但在 ChatGPT 中尚未提供。”但他们拒绝解释这些虚假网址。</p><p>我们不知道这种新体验何时可用，也不知道它的可靠性如何。 Despite this, news publishers continue to feed years of journalism into <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/time-strikes-a-deal-to-funnel-101-years-of-journalism-into-openais-gaping-maw-144058426.html"><ins>OpenAI&#39;s gaping maw</ins></a> in exchange for cold, hard cash because the journalism industry has <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.fastcompany.com/40534037/heres-an-abridged-timeline-of-digital-medias-pivot-to-video"><ins>consistently sucked</ins></a> at figuring out how to make money without <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-is-reportedly-paying-publishers-thousands-of-dollars-to-use-its-ai-to-write-stories-215943624.html"><ins>selling its soul</ins></a> to tech companies. Meanwhile, AI companies are <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/randalllane/2024/06/11/why-perplexitys-cynical-theft-represents-everything-that-could-go-wrong-with-ai/"><ins>chowing down</ins></a> on content published by anyone who hasn&#39;t signed these Faustian bargains and using it to train their models anyway. Mustafa Suleiman, Microsoft&#39;s AI head, <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://x.com/tsarnick/status/1805809836854329450"><ins>recently called</ins></a> anything published on the internet “freeware” that is fair game for training AI models.在我撰写本文时，微软的估值为 3.36 万亿美元。</p><p>这里有一个教训：如果 ChatGPT 编造了 URL，那么它也在编造事实。这就是生成式人工智能的工作原理——从本质上讲，该技术是自动完成的更高级版本，只需猜测序列中下一个看似合理的单词即可。它并不“理解”你所说的内容，尽管它的行为就像它那样。 Recently, I tried getting our leading chatbots to help me solve the <em>New York Times</em> Spelling Bee and watched them <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/if-ai-is-going-to-take-over-the-world-why-cant-it-solve-the-spelling-bee-170034469.html"><ins>crash and burn</ins></a> .<br><br>如果生成式人工智能甚至无法解决拼字比赛，那么你就不应该用它来获取事实。</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/please-dont-get-your-news-from-ai-chatbots-000027227.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/please-dont-get-your-news-from-ai-chatbots-000027227.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c97b2633-fd1b-4e20-aa90-bbe436904c47 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Pranav Dixit]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jun 2024 00:00:27 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1719532422</ingested><modified> 2024-06-27T23:53:48+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Books & Publishing]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Pranav Dixit]]></category><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F4cb7a880-9aca-11ee-847d-66d02252e855&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=4d9540b6f37ea57a3ea82c289906b9a65998325d" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F4cb7a880-9aca-11ee-847d-66d02252e855&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=9b9fb14f12f810c9ce8717b7c7c6425f31031f72" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[REUTERS / Reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[OpenAI CEO Sam Altman testifies before a Senate Judiciary Privacy, Technology & the Law Subcommittee hearing titled 'Oversight of A.I.: Rules for Artificial Intelligence' on Capitol Hill in Washington, U.S., May 16, 2023.  REUTERS/Elizabeth Frantz]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA['Oversight of A.I.: Rules for Artificial Intelligence' Subcommittee hearing in Washington]]></media:title></media:content></item></channel></rss>